nodes.documentation: @title Library to compute rounds and phases for an equal length commit-reveal voting cycle.
nodes.name: VoteTiming
init

nodes.documentation: @notice Gets the most recently stored round ID set by updateRoundId().
nodes.name: getLastUpdatedRoundId

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct VoteTiming.Data storage pointer,uint256) view returns (uint256,uint256)

nodes.documentation:
@notice Determines whether time has advanced far enough to advance to the next voting round and update the
stored round id.
nodes.name: shouldUpdateRoundId

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct VoteTiming.Data storage pointer,uint256) view returns (uint256,uint256)

nodes.documentation: @notice Updates the round id. Note: if shouldUpdateRoundId() returns false, this method will have no effect.
nodes.name: updateRoundId

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct VoteTiming.Data storage pointer,uint256) view returns (uint256,uint256)

nodes.documentation:
@notice Computes what the stored round id would be if it were updated right now, but this method does not
commit the update.
nodes.name: computeCurrentRoundId

nodes.documentation: @notice Computes the current phase based only on the current time.
nodes.name: computeCurrentPhase

nodes.documentation:
@notice Gets the end time of the current round or any round in the future. Note: this method will revert if
the roundId < getLastUpdatedRoundId().
nodes.name: computeEstimatedRoundEndTime

nodes.documentation: @dev Computes an updated round id and round start time based on the current time.
nodes.name: _getCurrentRoundIdAndStartTime
